{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The use of psychoactive substances](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3202501/) has been a part of human culture for thousands of years; drugs have been used for religious, medical or recreational purposes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Through legalising drugs within a finite border, the criminal economic chain could be controlled inside that border only.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Strict quality controls will stimulate a fair competition amongst drug suppliers to offer the purest drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addiction treatment isn't actually very expensive or costly, and is likely to be clinically simpler to resolve than is widely assumed."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Colorado, between 2014 and 2017, [over $500 million](https://money.cnn.com/2017/07/19/news/colorado-marijuana-tax-revenue/index.html) in government revenue was raised by taxes and fees on marijuana sales. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since access to drugs is limited, and alcohol is widely available, this is to be expected and not proof of success.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As long as the taxes don't surpass the higher costs of the black market businesses, there is no reason to believe that legal drugs would be more expensive. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug addiction and abuse are more related to mental health than legality. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Heroin users](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/what-are-medical-complications-chronic-heroin-use) experience mental disorders, such as depression, insomnia and antisocial personality disorder.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'No alcohol or tobacco company has openly killed anyone to continue selling their product.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tracing the rapist after the rape does not undo the rape itself, as the harm was already done.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising all drugs may give private companies incentives to advertise/promote the use of those, potentially leading to an increase the overall drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalising drugs related to date rape could bring the issue further into the public eye, allowing for more widespread education on the topic.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a false equivalency. Providing a service or good to bolster economic growth is not the same as being forced to give your money to the government.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One can imagine that an inebriated cannabis user may leave the house less often and therefore spend less money. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The highest tax estimates of marijuana legalisation reach[$28 billion](https://taxfoundation.org/marijuana-tax-legalization-federal-revenue/) from federal revenues, business taxes and income taxes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The same applies to already legal alcohol. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Removing support for someone mentally ill comes with costs. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs could make people live and learn life as it is. Bad decisions are a part of life.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of all drugs will promote newer, and safer drugs being developed to combat the negative side effects of dangerous drugs such as methamphetamines or heroin. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It will create jobs, not only in distribution but also in drug clinics and counseling centers. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It may be very difficult to diagnose which individuals suffer from self-inflicted mental illness or trauma and which ones are taking drugs as a result of their condition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the government cannot take responsibility for a dangerous activity which takes place in society, there is no guarantee anyone else will.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug prohibition might be inspired by some kind of racism but abandoning it would not necessarily mean an improvement of the situation for those incarcerated or addicted to drugs. There are still many other systematic racial issues unrelated to drug prohibition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Someone experiencing elevated stress levels isn't a good enough justification to limit other people's freedom by force. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Sensible legal drug policy would uses taxes to keep prices equal or slightly below current black market prices to keep that from occuring. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Just because there are other systematic racial issues does not mean we cannot challenge this particular racist law.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There are legal substances which have a much higher toxicity and legal substances which can be developed to be highly toxic. The possible use of drugs as weapons is irrelevant as there are much more dangerous substances freely available.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legislators should not be supporting or incentivising the use of any drug that leads to hallucinating and or violence. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Non-violent dangers could increase, such as syringes being left in parks and other public spaces. This would create a risk of disease and injury to anyone in the area, especially children. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A legalization of all drugs may lead to many [replacing](https://theintercept.com/2018/04/20/marijuana-legalization-alcohol-consumption/) part of their alcohol consumption with healthier drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Colorado, between 2014 and 2017, [over $500 million](https://money.cnn.com/2017/07/19/news/colorado-marijuana-tax-revenue/index.html) in government revenue was raised by taxes and fees on marijuana sales. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, in the USA, there is a [pharmaceutical opioid crisis](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/us-opioid-epidemic). Drug companies and legal policies cannot be trusted to protect citizens. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates negatively with socially-responsible behavior. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Nixon's war on drugs [was started](https://www.cnn.com/2016/03/23/politics/john-ehrlichman-richard-nixon-drug-war-blacks-hippie/index.html) to target blacks and hippies."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not a matter of being "viewed as" criminals: under a regime of criminalisation, drug users *are* criminals. It is not a matter of "feeling comfortable" seeking help, it\'s that seeking help would no longer carry the threat of actually going to prison. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}
